rently fuel public debate about stem cell research. One of the few books to provide a comprehensive overview for a wide audience, the volume brings together leading scientists, ethicists, political scientists, and doctors to explain this new scientific development and explore its ramifications.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aCellules souches embryonnairesxRecherchexAspect moralxÉtats-Unis. 0aCellules souches embryonnairesxRecherchexAspect politiquexÉtats-Unis. 0aCellules souches embryonnairesxRecherchexAspect religieuxxÉtats-Unis. 0aEmbryonic stem cellsxResearchxMoral and ethical aspectsxUnited States. 0aEmbryonic stem cellsxResearchxMoral and ethical aspectszUnited States. 0aEmbryonic stem cellsxResearchxPolitical aspectsxUnited States. 0aEmbryonic stem cellsxResearchxPolitical aspectszUnited States. 0aEmbryonic stem cellsxResearchxReligious aspectsxUnited States. 0aEmbryonic stem cellsxResearchzUnited StatesxReligious aspects. 7aMEDICAL / Health Policy.2bisacsh1 aMiller, Ronald, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMonroe, Kristen Renwick, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aTobis, Jerome, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package 2000-2015z978311066334108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520940994423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520940994.jpg  a978-3-11-066334-1  UC Press eBook Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-069042-2  UC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles